message: Considering the fact that there are mulitple cases where Sultans have been "elevated" to the title of King (Egypt in 1922, Nejd/Saudi Arabia in 1932 and Morocco in 1957) Sultan should not be listed as being superior to King. The Ottomans did not refer to their Emperor as Sultan, but rather Padishah or Sultan of Sultans.
